-- Federer Wins Second Set Against Tomas Berdych to Tie 1-1 in Quarterfinal
-- James Cone
-- 2010-06-30T13:22:33Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-30/federer-wins-second-set-against-tomas-berdych-to-tie-1-1-in-quarterfinal.html

          
          
             Defending champion Roger Federer won
the second set against Tomas Berdych today to tie their
Wimbledon tennis quarterfinal at 1-1.  
 The Swiss, seeking to tie Pete Sampras’s Open era men’s
record of seven titles at the All England Club, took the set 6-
3. Berdych of the Czech Republic won the opener 6-4 on Centre
Court today.  
 Federer is ranked No. 2 on the ATP Tour, although is seeded
No. 1 at Wimbledon.  
          
          


  


        